This is the homepage of your **Team Wiki**!

- [Introduction to Functional Programming](#/pages/4/show)
- [Understanding Single-Page Applications](#/pages/1/show)

Happy collaborating!

pages.title: Understanding Single Page Applications
pages.content:
## Overview
Single Page Applications (SPAs) are web applications that load a single HTML page and dynamically update content as the user interacts with the app.

## Key Features
- Improved user experience by avoiding full page reloads.
- Heavy use of JavaScript frameworks like React, Angular, or Vue.
- REST or GraphQL APIs commonly used for backend communication.

## When to Use SPAs
- When responsiveness and performance are key.
- For applications like dashboards, mail clients, or social media platforms.

## Best Practices
1. Use client-side routing responsibly.
2. Implement proper loading states.
3. Ensure SEO through pre-rendering or server-side rendering.

## References
- [MDN on SPAs](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/SPA)
- [React Documentation](https://reactjs.org/)

## Summary
| Aspect           | Description                    |
|------------------|--------------------------------|
| Type             | Frontend Architecture          |
| Common Tools     | React, Angular, Vue            |
| Drawbacks        | SEO and initial load complexity|
| Recommended Use  | Interactive web applications   |

pages.title: Introduction to TCP/IP
pages.content:
## Overview
TCP/IP (Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol) is the foundational communication protocol suite for the internet and most local networks.

## Layers of TCP/IP
1. **Application Layer**  Interfaces for applications to access network services.
2. **Transport Layer**  Manages end-to-end communication (TCP, UDP).
3. **Internet Layer**  Handles logical addressing and routing (IP).
4. **Network Access Layer**  Deals with hardware addressing and media access.

## Features
- Connection-oriented and connectionless protocols
- IP addressing and subnetting
- Reliable data transmission

## Use Cases
- Internet browsing
- Email services
- File transfers

## References
- [RFC 1180](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1180)
- [Cisco TCP/IP Guide](https://www.cisco.com/)

## Summary
| Layer              | Protocols       |
|--------------------|-----------------|
| Application        | HTTP, FTP, DNS  |
| Transport          | TCP, UDP        |
| Internet           | IP, ICMP        |
| Network Access     | Ethernet, Wi-Fi |

pages.title: Building Cross-Platform Mobile Apps
pages.content:
## Overview
Cross-platform mobile development allows developers to write code once and deploy it on both Android and iOS. This can significantly reduce time and cost.

## Popular Frameworks
- **React Native**  Uses JavaScript and React.
- **Flutter**  Uses Dart and provides a rich set of widgets.
- **Xamarin**  Uses C# and integrates with Visual Studio.

## Advantages
- Code reuse across platforms
- Faster development cycles
- Unified UI/UX strategy

## Challenges
- Platform-specific bugs
- Performance issues
- Dependency on third-party libraries

## Use Cases
- Startups with limited resources
- MVP development
- Internal business apps

## References
- [React Native Docs](https://reactnative.dev/)
- [Flutter.dev](https://flutter.dev/)

## Summary
| Tool        | Language | Notable Feature       |
|-------------|----------|------------------------|
| React Native| JS       | Native components      |
| Flutter     | Dart     | High-performance UI    |
| Xamarin     | C#       | Microsoft ecosystem    |

pages.title: Introduction to Functional Programming
pages.content:
## Overview
Functional programming is a programming paradigm that treats computation as the evaluation of mathematical functions and avoids changing state or mutable data.

## Key Concepts
- Pure functions
- Immutability
- Higher-order functions
- Recursion

## Benefits
- Easier to reason about code
- Better modularity
- Enhanced concurrency

## Common Languages
- Haskell
- Scala
- Elixir
- F#

## Use Cases
- Data transformation pipelines
- Concurrent systems

## References
- [Functional Programming Principles](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Functional_programming)
- [Learn You a Haskell](http://learnyouahaskell.com/)

## Summary
| Concept          | Description                          |
|------------------|------------------------------------|
| Pure Functions   | No side effects                    |
| Immutability     | Data cannot be changed             |
| Higher-Order     | Functions that take/return functions|
| Recursion        | Functions calling themselves       |

pages.title: Overview of Emerging Technologies
pages.content:
## Introduction
Emerging technologies are innovations that are currently developing or will be developed over the next few years, impacting industries and society.

## Key Areas
- Artificial Intelligence (AI)
- Quantum Computing
- Blockchain
- Internet of Things (IoT)

## Potential Impacts
- Automation of tasks
- Enhanced data processing
- New business models

## Challenges
- Ethical concerns
- Security risks
- Regulatory hurdles

## References
- [Gartner Hype Cycle](https://www.gartner.com/en/research/methodologies/gartner-hype-cycle)
- [IEEE Emerging Tech](https://technology.ieee.org/)

## Summary
| Technology         | Description                         |
|--------------------|-----------------------------------|
| AI                 | Machines simulating human tasks   |
| Quantum Computing   | Computing using quantum bits       |
| Blockchain         | Decentralized digital ledger      |
| IoT                | Network of connected devices      |

pages.title: Modern Frontend Development
pages.content:
## Introduction
Frontend development focuses on the part of a website or web application that users interact with directly.

### Importance of User Experience (UX)
Good frontend design enhances user engagement and satisfaction.

## Core Technologies

### HTML
HTML structures the content of web pages.

### CSS
CSS styles and visually formats the content.

### JavaScript
JavaScript adds interactivity and dynamic behavior.

## Frameworks and Libraries

### React
A JavaScript library for building user interfaces using components.

### Vue.js
A progressive framework for building UI with ease of integration.

### Angular
A full-featured framework maintained by Google.

## Best Practices

### Responsive Design
Ensures the website works on all devices and screen sizes.

### Performance Optimization
Minimize load times by optimizing assets and code.

### Accessibility
Make websites usable for people with disabilities.

## References
- [MDN Web Docs](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Front-end_web_developer)
- [React Official](https://reactjs.org/)

## Summary
| Technology | Role              |
|------------|-------------------|
| HTML       | Structure         |
| CSS        | Styling           |
| JavaScript | Interactivity     |

TCP/IP is a suite of protocols used for communication across interconnected networks. It breaks down communication into layers for scalability and flexibility.

Includes protocols like:

- IP
- TCP

Used in nearly all digital communications today.
